<item>
            <title>[DAEMON-164] tomcat windows service name can&apos;t contain spaces</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DAEMON-164</link>
                <project id="12310468" key="DAEMON">Commons Daemon</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If I try to install tomcat as a service and use a service name (not a display&lt;br/&gt;
name) that contains spaces or underscores it fails:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;C:\Program Files (x86)\comp\apache-tomcat\bin\tomcat6.exe //IS//Comp Service&lt;br/&gt;
or&lt;br/&gt;
C:\Program Files (x86)\comp\apache-tomcat\bin\tomcat6.exe //IS//Comp_Service&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;All the other windows service have spaces so I want mine to be consistent.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12467252">DAEMON-164</key>
            <summary>tomcat windows service name can&apos;t contain spaces</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=21133&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Bug</type>
                                            <priority id="3" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/priorities/major.svg">Major</priority>
                        <status id="6" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/statuses/closed.png" description="The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are not closed can be reopened.">Closed</status>
                    <statusCategory id="3" key="done" colorName="green"/>
                                    <resolution id="1">Fixed</resolution>
                                        <assignee username="-1">Unassigned</assignee>
                                    <reporter username="jkenny3112000@yahoo.com">John Kenny</reporter>
                        <labels>
                    </labels>
                <created>Thu, 17 Jun 2010 19:04:58 +0000</created>
                <updated>Tue, 19 Oct 2010 18:41:14 +0000</updated>
                            <resolved>Sat, 2 Oct 2010 10:46:26 +0000</resolved>
                                                    <fixVersion>1.0.4</fixVersion>
                                    <component>Procrun</component>
                        <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>0</watches>
                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12917182" author="mturk@apache.org" created="Sat, 2 Oct 2010 10:46:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Partially fixed in the SVN.&lt;br/&gt;
Underscores are allowed but spaces are not, neither it will be.&lt;br/&gt;
Reason is because service name is used to guess the executable which would in that&lt;br/&gt;
case need to have spaces as well and the command line parser uses space as delimiter&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Anyhow will be part of 1.0.4&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12917197" author="mturk@apache.org" created="Sat, 2 Oct 2010 14:35:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Update:&lt;br/&gt;
Space is allowed as service name.&lt;br/&gt;
Note that in that case you will have to use the prunsrv.exe &quot;//IS//foo bar&quot; if you wish your service name is &quot;foo bar&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
However the limitation is imposed that name consists only of valid windows file naming convention&lt;br/&gt;
which says invalid characters are:&lt;br/&gt;
&quot;&amp;lt; &amp;gt; : &quot; / \ | ? *&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
The reason is because we use service name as a synonym for the executable name (without .exe),&lt;br/&gt;
so the service name must contain the same character set allowed by the file naming convention.&lt;/p&gt;

</comment>
                    </comments>
                    <attachments>
                    </attachments>
