                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If you want start a Java service on a 64 bit Windows 7 with &quot;Use default&quot; Java VM then the service does not start. In the log you can see the follow output. If you set the VM to the default 64 bit VM then all is ok. It look like that the VM can not be found. A look in the registry show that all entries are ok for the 64 bit tree of JavaSoft.&lt;/p&gt;


