<item>
            <title>[DAEMON-133] The field SimpleDaemon.stopping is accessed from multiple threads without synch.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DAEMON-133</link>
                <project id="12310468" key="DAEMON">Commons Daemon</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The field SimpleDaemon.stopping is accessed from multiple threads without synchronisation.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The field is access from the run() and stop() methods, and should either be made volatile, or should should be accessed from a synchronized block.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;WIthout such synch, the run() method may never see the value set by the stop() method.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12457042">DAEMON-133</key>
            <summary>The field SimpleDaemon.stopping is accessed from multiple threads without synch.</summary>
