<item>
            <title>[DAEMON-126] Log on tab of Prunmgr ignores current settings</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DAEMON-126</link>
                <project id="12310468" key="DAEMON">Commons Daemon</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This was &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=38516&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=38516&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If a valid user and password is specified in the &quot;log on&quot; tab of Prunmgr  then if Prunmgr is closed and re-opened, the log on tab shows the log on as local system account even though the service is configured to start as a specified user. This also makes it impossible to restore the service to use a local system account through the log in tab.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The workaround is to use the standard windows service gui.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
