<item>
            <title>[DAEMON-88] JMX java options can cause silent service failure</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DAEMON-88</link>
                <project id="12310468" key="DAEMON">Commons Daemon</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;See &lt;a href=&quot;http://issues.apache.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=35635&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://issues.apache.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=35635&lt;/a&gt; for the full history.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Short version is:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Install 5.5.20&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;add -Dcom.sun.management.jmxremote.port=5555 and -Dcom.sun.management.jmxremote.password.file=C:\jmxremote.password to Java Options&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Try to start the service&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;The service fails to start and creates only zero byte log files&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12352158">DAEMON-88</key>
            <summary>JMX java options can cause silent service failure</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=21133&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Bug</type>
                                            <priority id="3" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/priorities/major.svg">Major</priority>
                        <status id="6" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/statuses/closed.png" description="The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are not closed can be reopened.">Closed</status>
                    <statusCategory id="3" key="done" colorName="green"/>
                                    <resolution id="2">Won&apos;t Fix</resolution>
                                        <assignee username="-1">Unassigned</assignee>
                                    <reporter username="markt">Mark Thomas</reporter>
                        <labels>
                    </labels>
                <created>Mon, 2 Oct 2006 04:18:47 +0000</created>
                <updated>Tue, 14 Nov 2017 14:40:51 +0000</updated>
                            <resolved>Tue, 14 Nov 2017 14:40:51 +0000</resolved>
                                                                    <component>Procrun</component>
                        <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>0</watches>
                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12456684" author="billbarker" created="Fri, 8 Dec 2006 03:46:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Unless you have NTFS, that won&apos;t work on Windows.  Yes, logging could be better.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12832591" author="mturk@apache.org" created="Thu, 11 Feb 2010 17:34:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Not a bug, since the arguments containing spaces must be properly quoted&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12862709" author="genialmaniac" created="Fri, 30 Apr 2010 15:21:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m facing the same problem and it still not resolved, 5.5.20 with 1.6.0_10 jre, cannot run jmxremote control with security enable.&lt;br/&gt;
tried:&lt;br/&gt;
apache tomcat service run under SERVICE_TOMCAT_ACCOUNT&lt;br/&gt;
jmxremote.password own by  SERVICE_TOMCAT_ACCOUNT and read only for him permission.&lt;br/&gt;
no way, still same error 1067, cannot see why cause no java trace is provided about error.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So I really think this bug is not solved. Consequences is jmx without security behind firewall.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12862836" author="sebb@apache.org" created="Fri, 30 Apr 2010 19:57:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The version of the code currently in SVN does report problems to the stderr file, e.g. I have seen:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Error: Password file not found:&lt;br/&gt;
Error: Password file read access must be restricted:&lt;br/&gt;
Error: Failed in reading the password file:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, there is no error logged to the commons-daemon log, even with debug logging.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think that should be corrected, so re-opening issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12862840" author="sebb@apache.org" created="Fri, 30 Apr 2010 20:03:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@genialmaniac&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you can run a script as SERVICE_TOMCAT_ACCOUNT you might be able to debug the problem as follows:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;java -Dcom.sun.management.jmxremote.port=5555 -Dcom.sun.management.jmxremote.password.file=jmx.txt dummy&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Copy the above directly from the Tomcat settings.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If there are any errors with the password file or its protection, it seems that these will be reported even before the dummy class is opened, so it does not have to be present.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;Of course you could created a simple class file to test with too&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12922870" author="mturk@apache.org" created="Wed, 20 Oct 2010 06:41:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The current trunk for&lt;br/&gt;
++JvmOptons &quot;-Dcom.sun.management.jmxremote.port=5555;-Dcom.sun.management.jmxremote.password.file=jmx.txt&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
displays in the service-stderr-&amp;lt;DATE&amp;gt;.log the following&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2010-10-20 08:34:11 Commons Daemon procrun stderr initialized&lt;br/&gt;
Error: Password file not found: jmx.txt&lt;br/&gt;
(Running jboss-5.0)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Since those directives fails to initialize the JVM itself, I see no way of making that more verbose&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    </comments>
