<item>
            <title>[DAEMON-67] signal handling on Solaris 5.8</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DAEMON-67</link>
                <project id="12310468" key="DAEMON">Commons Daemon</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;in the handler() function (jsvc-unix.c) is after catching the relevant signal&lt;br/&gt;
the flag stopping set and the handler tries to call itself once again (over the&lt;br/&gt;
func.pointer handler_xxx). In this case, the stop/restart daemon doesn&apos;t work&lt;br/&gt;
correctly on Solaris, and ends with a status 143 (129) instead of 0 (123),&lt;br/&gt;
without calling a java_stop()/java_destroy(). &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If those duplicate calls from handler are removed, the daemon stop/restart works&lt;br/&gt;
fine and correct.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Operating System: Solaris&lt;br/&gt;
Platform: Sun&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
        <key id="12341063">DAEMON-67</key>
            <summary>signal handling on Solaris 5.8</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=21133&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Bug</type>
                                            <priority id="3" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/priorities/major.svg">Major</priority>
                        <status id="6" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/statuses/closed.png" description="The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are not closed can be reopened.">Closed</status>
                    <statusCategory id="3" key="done" colorName="green"/>
                                    <resolution id="1">Fixed</resolution>
                                        <assignee username="-1">Unassigned</assignee>
                                    <reporter username="peter.poloha@nextra.sk">Peter Poloha</reporter>
                        <labels>
                    </labels>
                <created>Thu, 30 Oct 2003 18:24:27 +0000</created>
                <updated>Tue, 14 Nov 2017 14:47:22 +0000</updated>
                            <resolved>Tue, 14 Nov 2017 14:47:22 +0000</resolved>
                                    <version>1.0 Alpha</version>
                                    <fixVersion>1.0.2</fixVersion>
                                        <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>0</watches>
                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12405363" author="william.barker@wilshire.com" created="Mon, 3 Nov 2003 06:59:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Created an attachment (id=8874)&lt;br/&gt;
Patch that prevents the double-callback&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12405364" author="william.barker@wilshire.com" created="Wed, 31 Dec 2003 13:03:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed now in the CVS, and should appear in the next release.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
