<item>
            <title>[DAEMON-62] [daemon] Cannot pass more than one startup parameter</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DAEMON-62</link>
                <project id="12310468" key="DAEMON">Commons Daemon</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In contrast to the documentation procrun doesn&apos;t recognize more parameter &lt;br/&gt;
supplied in --StartupClass and --ShutdownClass, it always passes a single &lt;br/&gt;
parameter. I also checked the source code and it seems to me that such kind of &lt;br/&gt;
functionality is not implemented at all.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here is the current doc:&lt;br/&gt;
--StartupClass 	Class name that will be called if started from JVM when the &lt;br/&gt;
application s starts. The method name is separated by semicolon after the class &lt;br/&gt;
name. ***The parameters passed to the class method are semicolon separated &lt;br/&gt;
values after the method name.*** For example: org/apache/jk/apr/TomcatStarter;&lt;br/&gt;
Main;start&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Operating System: Windows XP&lt;br/&gt;
Platform: Other&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
        <key id="12341452">DAEMON-62</key>
            <summary>[daemon] Cannot pass more than one startup parameter</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=21133&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Bug</type>
                                            <priority id="3" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/priorities/major.svg">Major</priority>
                        <status id="6" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/statuses/closed.png" description="The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are not closed can be reopened.">Closed</status>
                    <statusCategory id="3" key="done" colorName="green"/>
                                    <resolution id="1">Fixed</resolution>
                                        <assignee username="-1">Unassigned</assignee>
                                    <reporter username="hontvari2@solware.com">Hontvari Jozsef</reporter>
                        <labels>
                    </labels>
                <created>Mon, 17 May 2004 17:40:45 +0000</created>
                <updated>Tue, 14 Nov 2017 15:05:43 +0000</updated>
                            <resolved>Tue, 14 Nov 2017 15:05:43 +0000</resolved>
                                    <version>1.0</version>
                                    <fixVersion>1.0.2</fixVersion>
                                        <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>0</watches>
                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12406614" author="mturk@apache.org" created="Sun, 17 Apr 2005 18:27:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Multiple params are passed to the startup class.&lt;br/&gt;
Set the LogLevel to debug and you will see the argv params passed&lt;br/&gt;
