                            <comment id="12411581" author="stefan.vogel@med.ge.com" created="Fri, 10 Mar 2006 19:23:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Created an attachment (id=17863)&lt;br/&gt;
Proposed implementation&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The attached proposed fix checks the service name length (maxium 256) and that&lt;br/&gt;
there are is no slash or backslash in the service name.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please incorporate. Thanks&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12411582" author="stefan.vogel@med.ge.com" created="Fri, 10 Mar 2006 20:31:41 +0000"  >&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DAEMON-21&quot; title=&quot;[daemon] prunsrv prohibits non-alphanumeric characters in service names&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DAEMON-21&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;COM-2814&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; has been marked as a duplicate of this bug. ***&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="12411583" author="stefan.vogel@med.ge.com" created="Fri, 10 Mar 2006 22:55:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;(From update of attachment 17863)&lt;br/&gt;
service.c&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12411584" author="stefan.vogel@med.ge.com" created="Fri, 10 Mar 2006 22:55:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;(From update of attachment 17863)&lt;br/&gt;
service.c&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12411585" author="stefan.vogel@med.ge.com" created="Fri, 10 Mar 2006 22:59:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Created an attachment (id=17865)&lt;br/&gt;
Proposed implementation (part2)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A further change is required, in prunsrv.c, putting double-quotes around the&lt;br/&gt;
//RS//&amp;lt;servicename&amp;gt; part of the ImagePath. Otherwise the service will not start&lt;br/&gt;
when &amp;lt;servicename&amp;gt; contains blanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12411586" author="stefan.vogel@med.ge.com" created="Thu, 23 Mar 2006 17:45:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Created an attachment (id=17948)&lt;br/&gt;
diff -u describing changes in service.c&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12411587" author="stefan.vogel@med.ge.com" created="Thu, 23 Mar 2006 17:57:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Created an attachment (id=17949)&lt;br/&gt;
diff -u describing changes in prunsrv.c&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12832549" author="mturk@apache.org" created="Thu, 11 Feb 2010 16:20:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Apart from academic, allowing spaces in service names makes no real value&lt;br/&gt;
and just complicates the parameter handling by requirement to properly quote&lt;br/&gt;
the arguments and service name processing.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There is service description which can be used to enter whatever description needed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    </comments>
