<item>
            <title>[DAEMON-48] [daemon] tomcat5.exe crashes</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DAEMON-48</link>
                <project id="12310468" key="DAEMON">Commons Daemon</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;tomcat5.exe (a.k.a. Commons Daemon&apos;s prunsrv.exe) version 2.0.0.0 crashes when&lt;br/&gt;
started as a service with &quot;Environment&quot; variables that do not contain &quot;%&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Reason:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;prunsrv.c line 365: apxFree(e) crashes&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;because&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;prunsrv.c line 363: e = apxExpandStrW(gPool, p)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;may return input parameter &quot;p&quot; instead of newly allocated.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Operating System: All&lt;br/&gt;
Platform: PC&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
        <key id="12342308">DAEMON-48</key>
            <summary>[daemon] tomcat5.exe crashes</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=21133&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Bug</type>
                                            <priority id="3" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/priorities/major.svg">Major</priority>
                        <status id="6" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/statuses/closed.png" description="The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are not closed can be reopened.">Closed</status>
                    <statusCategory id="3" key="done" colorName="green"/>
                                    <resolution id="1">Fixed</resolution>
                                        <assignee username="-1">Unassigned</assignee>
                                    <reporter username="tschleu@canto.de">Thomas Schleu</reporter>
                        <labels>
                    </labels>
                <created>Tue, 14 Jun 2005 21:13:14 +0000</created>
                <updated>Tue, 14 Nov 2017 15:05:51 +0000</updated>
                            <resolved>Tue, 14 Nov 2017 15:05:51 +0000</resolved>
                                    <version>1.0.1</version>
                                    <fixVersion>1.0.2</fixVersion>
                                        <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>0</watches>
                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12409611" author="robert_longson@standardandpoors.com" created="Thu, 16 Jun 2005 19:22:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Created an attachment (id=15435)&lt;br/&gt;
Need to create new strings on the heap in all cases&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In some cases apxExpandStrA and apxExpandStrW create new strings on the heap&lt;br/&gt;
(if there is a %) and dont if there is not. The caller in prunsrv.c always&lt;br/&gt;
frees the string and so if there is no % it then crashes. The fix makes&lt;br/&gt;
apxExpandStr(A/W) create new strings on the heap in all cases.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Tested by setting SO_ENVIRONMENT=KEY=VALUE then installing and running the&lt;br/&gt;
service&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
