<item>
            <title>[DAEMON-47] [daemon][PATCH] Make jsvc delete pid file on daemon exit</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DAEMON-47</link>
                <project id="12310468" key="DAEMON">Commons Daemon</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The attached patch updates jsvc to cause it to delete the pid file on exit of the daemon process. This &lt;br/&gt;
greatly eases and strengthens checking of whether the daemon process is still alive.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Because the daemon has dropped priviledges by the time it wants to exit, it is no longer able, itself, to &lt;br/&gt;
delete the pid file as it&apos;s likely lost priviledges to the pid location. I moved creation/deleting of the pid &lt;br/&gt;
file to the controller process: the controller creates the pid file when the child is forked, and deletes it &lt;br/&gt;
when the child terminates.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Operating System: other&lt;br/&gt;
Platform: Other&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
        <key id="12341795">DAEMON-47</key>
