<item>
            <title>[DAEMON-38] [daemon] jar2exe.c does not compile</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DAEMON-38</link>
                <project id="12310468" key="DAEMON">Commons Daemon</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;apxJavaInitialize had an additional argument added, BOOL bReduceSignals under&lt;br/&gt;
revision 140800. jar2exe.c was not modified to call apxJavaInitialise with this&lt;br/&gt;
additional argument and no longer compiles. Previously apxJavaInitialize always&lt;br/&gt;
executed the reduce signals code, now it does so only if bReduceSignals is TRUE.&lt;br/&gt;
According to the documentation this argument should be TRUE if the code is&lt;br/&gt;
running as a service and FALSE otherwise. As I don&apos;t think jar2exe runs as a&lt;br/&gt;
service I think FALSE is the appropriate value for this argument.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Operating System: other&lt;br/&gt;
Platform: PC&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
        <key id="12342321">DAEMON-38</key>
