<item>
            <title>[DAEMON-34] [daemon] prunsrv timeouts &gt; 1 minute don&apos;t work</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DAEMON-34</link>
                <project id="12310468" key="DAEMON">Commons Daemon</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;On Windows the maximum amount of time a service can take to die is held in the&lt;br/&gt;
registry as&lt;br/&gt;
HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Control\WaitToKillServiceTimeout&lt;br/&gt;
prunsrv should not wait any longer than this to shutdown, otherwise it will be&lt;br/&gt;
killed anyway.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Operating System: other&lt;br/&gt;
Platform: PC&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
        <key id="12342329">DAEMON-34</key>
            <summary>[daemon] prunsrv timeouts &gt; 1 minute don&apos;t work</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=21133&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Bug</type>
                                            <priority id="3" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/priorities/major.svg">Major</priority>
                        <status id="6" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/statuses/closed.png" description="The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are not closed can be reopened.">Closed</status>
                    <statusCategory id="3" key="done" colorName="green"/>
                                    <resolution id="1">Fixed</resolution>
                                        <assignee username="-1">Unassigned</assignee>
                                    <reporter username="robert_longson@standardandpoors.com">Robert Longson</reporter>
                        <labels>
                    </labels>
                <created>Tue, 21 Jun 2005 22:59:16 +0000</created>
                <updated>Tue, 14 Nov 2017 15:05:55 +0000</updated>
                            <resolved>Tue, 14 Nov 2017 15:05:55 +0000</resolved>
                                    <version>1.0.1</version>
                                    <fixVersion>1.0.2</fixVersion>
                                        <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>0</watches>
                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12409658" author="robert_longson@standardandpoors.com" created="Tue, 21 Jun 2005 23:01:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Created an attachment (id=15498)&lt;br/&gt;
add function to read the WaitToKillServiceTimeout&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12409659" author="robert_longson@standardandpoors.com" created="Tue, 21 Jun 2005 23:02:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Created an attachment (id=15499)&lt;br/&gt;
add function to read the WaitToKillServiceTimeout&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12409660" author="robert_longson@standardandpoors.com" created="Tue, 21 Jun 2005 23:08:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Created an attachment (id=15500)&lt;br/&gt;
read WaitToKillServiceTimeout and only wait that long&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12409661" author="robert_longson@standardandpoors.com" created="Wed, 22 Jun 2005 18:48:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Created an attachment (id=15510)&lt;br/&gt;
ensure we finish just before the OS kills us&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12409662" author="robert_longson@standardandpoors.com" created="Wed, 20 Jul 2005 19:39:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Created an attachment (id=15717)&lt;br/&gt;
creates a thread to stop the service so we don&apos;t get killed by the OS&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Without this fix timeouts of &amp;gt; 1 minute don&apos;t work (at least on Windows XP).&lt;br/&gt;
The OS thinks that the service is stuck and kills it. Timeout errors appear in&lt;br/&gt;
the NT event log. &lt;br/&gt;
The service_control_handler needs to return so the calling OS thread can&lt;br/&gt;
monitor the service stopping. Shutdown needs to happen in another thread.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12409663" author="robert_longson@standardandpoors.com" created="Wed, 20 Jul 2005 20:25:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Created an attachment (id=15718)&lt;br/&gt;
correction to shutdown time&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12409664" author="robert_longson@standardandpoors.com" created="Fri, 19 Aug 2005 20:43:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Created an attachment (id=16112)&lt;br/&gt;
new patch as this file has changed in CVS in the same function&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12481948" author="mturk@apache.org" created="Sun, 18 Mar 2007 15:05:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commited. Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    </comments>
                    <attachments>
