<item>
            <title>[DAEMON-29] [daemon] Changes to make jsvc work on AMD64 w/ JDK 1.5</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DAEMON-29</link>
                <project id="12310468" key="DAEMON">Commons Daemon</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I had to make two small changes to get jsvc to work on an AMD Opteron &lt;br/&gt;
machine running Linus using Sun&apos;s JDK 1.5 for AMD 64.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1. The CPU wasn&apos;t supported.  It is reported as x86_64 but the JDK labels it amd64&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2. The search paths for the jvm.cfg and libjvm.so do not match the JDK 1.5.  I&lt;br/&gt;
   added two search paths to fix that.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Operating System: other&lt;br/&gt;
Platform: Other&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
