<item>
            <title>[DAEMON-27] Partial support of space characters in Service Name</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DAEMON-27</link>
                <project id="12310468" key="DAEMON">Commons Daemon</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When you install a service, using this syntax:&lt;br/&gt;
 tomcat.exe //IS//&quot;Tomcat 5.0.14&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
Everything looks fine, except that in the Windows service properties,&lt;br/&gt;
the &quot;Path to executable&quot; is:&lt;br/&gt;
 tomcat.exe //RS//Tomcat 5.0.14&lt;br/&gt;
As the quotes are missing, only //RS//Tomcat is read, and this service&lt;br/&gt;
is not found.&lt;br/&gt;
If you manually add the quotes afterwards, the start can be achieved.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Workaround: Use only one word, such as Tomcat5014, until the bug is fixed.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Operating System: All&lt;br/&gt;
Platform: PC&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
