<item>
            <title>[DAEMON-26] service.bat  Does Not Accept Dash in Service Name</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DAEMON-26</link>
                <project id="12310468" key="DAEMON">Commons Daemon</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When running the service.bat script in tomcat/bin, I&apos;ve observed &quot;Overlapped IO&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
errors.  I believe the message originates from the Microsoft Service Control&lt;br/&gt;
Manager (SCM).  The defect may be an issue with the procrun commons utility.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Examples that work:&lt;br/&gt;
service install &lt;br/&gt;
service install beavisApp&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Examples that fail:&lt;br/&gt;
service install beavisApp-tomcat&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Operating System: All&lt;br/&gt;
Platform: PC&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
        <key id="12341463">DAEMON-26</key>
            <summary>service.bat  Does Not Accept Dash in Service Name</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=21133&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Bug</type>
                                            <priority id="4" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/priorities/minor.svg">Minor</priority>
                        <status id="6" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/statuses/closed.png" description="The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are not closed can be reopened.">Closed</status>
                    <statusCategory id="3" key="done" colorName="green"/>
                                    <resolution id="4">Incomplete</resolution>
                                        <assignee username="-1">Unassigned</assignee>
                                    <reporter username="brandall@cisco.com">Bill</reporter>
                        <labels>
                    </labels>
                <created>Thu, 20 May 2004 00:11:49 +0000</created>
                <updated>Wed, 7 Feb 2007 00:57:34 +0000</updated>
                            <resolved>Wed, 7 Feb 2007 00:57:34 +0000</resolved>
                                    <version>1.0 Alpha</version>
                                                        <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>0</watches>
                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12406646" author="yoavs@computer.org" created="Fri, 11 Jun 2004 07:04:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yup, it doesn&apos;t work with hyphens.  Here&apos;s the error message (Tomcat 5.0.26, &lt;br/&gt;
Windows XP Pro):&lt;br/&gt;
C:\jakarta-tomcat-5.0.26\bin&amp;gt;service.bat install beavisApp-tomcat&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;2004-06-10 19:58:25&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;349  prunsrv.c&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;error&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
The system cannot find the file specified.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;2004-06-10 19:58:25&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1037 prunsrv.c&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;error&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Load configuration failed&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;2004-06-10 19:58:26&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;349  prunsrv.c&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;error&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
The system cannot find the file specified.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;2004-06-10 19:58:26&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1037 prunsrv.c&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;error&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Load configuration failed&lt;br/&gt;
The service &apos;beavisApp-tomcat&apos; has been installed&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;prunsrv.c is at &lt;a href=&quot;http://cvs.apache.org/viewcvs.cgi/jakarta-&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://cvs.apache.org/viewcvs.cgi/jakarta-&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
commons/daemon/src/native/nt/procrun/apps/prunsrv/prunsrv.c, so I concur with &lt;br/&gt;
your theory that this is a procrun problem.  As such, I&apos;m going to reassign &lt;br/&gt;
this issue to the commons-daemon module.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12406647" author="mturk@apache.org" created="Fri, 11 Jun 2004 12:57:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Windows NT services does not allow to have a dash in it&apos;s names, as well as&lt;br/&gt;
forward or backward slash characters.&lt;br/&gt;
Use the beavisApp_tomcat instead.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    </comments>
