<item>
            <title>[DAEMON-14] [daemon] Installation failed</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DAEMON-14</link>
                <project id="12310468" key="DAEMON">Commons Daemon</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I downloaded the file jakarta-tomcat-5.0.28.exe and run it to install tomcat 5.0&lt;br/&gt;
I got no error (or any other) messages during the installation. On the last &lt;br/&gt;
page of the install-wizard I selected &quot;Run Tomcat&quot;. I get only the following &lt;br/&gt;
error dialog: &quot;Application System Error: Unable to open the Service Manager&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
The same happens if I want to call &quot;Configure Tomcat&quot; or &quot;Monitor Tomcat&quot; from &lt;br/&gt;
the program menu or if I start tomcat5w.exe in CATALINA_HOME/bin . &lt;br/&gt;
I ran the installation as a &quot;normal&quot; windows-user, and not as the Administrator.&lt;br/&gt;
I use java 1.4. &lt;br/&gt;
I have 2 other Tomcat versions on this PC (V4.x) both of them working.&lt;br/&gt;
Maybe the following error message helps to localise the bug:&lt;br/&gt;
If I start the program tomcat5.exe in CATALINA_HOME/bin in a command window I &lt;br/&gt;
get the following message:&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt;&amp;gt;  C:\Programme\Apache Group\Tomcat 5.0\bin&amp;gt;tomcat5.exe&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt;&amp;gt;  &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;2004-11-23 15:36:37&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;349  prunsrv.c&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;error&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt;&amp;gt;  Das System kann die angegebene Datei nicht finden.  &lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt;&amp;gt;  &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;2004-11-23 15:36:37&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1037 prunsrv.c&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;error&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt;&amp;gt;  Load configuration failed&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The first message translated from German: File could not be found&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I can only start my Tomcat5 using the startup scripts in CATALINA_HOME/bin &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/sad.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Operating System: Windows 2000&lt;br/&gt;
Platform: PC&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
        <key id="12341887">DAEMON-14</key>
            <summary>[daemon] Installation failed</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=21133&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Bug</type>
                                            <priority id="3" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/priorities/major.svg">Major</priority>
                        <status id="5" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/statuses/resolved.png" description="A resolution has been taken, and it is awaiting verification by reporter. From here issues are either reopened, or are closed.">Resolved</status>
                    <statusCategory id="3" key="done" colorName="green"/>
                                    <resolution id="2">Won&apos;t Fix</resolution>
                                        <assignee username="-1">Unassigned</assignee>
                                    <reporter username="judith@foeglein.de">Judith Foeglein</reporter>
                        <labels>
                    </labels>
                <created>Wed, 24 Nov 2004 00:23:09 +0000</created>
                <updated>Thu, 11 Feb 2010 17:30:12 +0000</updated>
                            <resolved>Thu, 11 Feb 2010 17:30:12 +0000</resolved>
                                                                        <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>0</watches>
                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12408143" author="yoavs@computer.org" created="Wed, 24 Nov 2004 00:35:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Installation of the 5.0.28 .exe distro on Win2K using JDK 1.4 has worked for me &lt;br/&gt;
numerous times without a problem.  The only difference I see between us is the &lt;br/&gt;
locale (mine is the default en_us).  However, this would go as a Commons-Daemon &lt;br/&gt;
issue and not a Tomcat issue, so I&apos;m changing the Component accordingly.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12408144" author="lucisandor@gmail.com" created="Thu, 27 Jan 2005 11:32:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have a similar problem when launching Tomcat&apos;s Service Manager (tomcat5w.exe).&lt;br/&gt;
I don&apos;t get console output, but a message box saying &quot;Application System Error.&lt;br/&gt;
Access is denied. Unable to open the Service Manager. &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;OK&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&quot;. This error occured&lt;br/&gt;
each time I logged on my usual account, which is a Power User.&lt;br/&gt;
When I runas from command prompt or &quot;Run As..&quot; from Start menu or Explorer with&lt;br/&gt;
an Administrator account, things work out OK.&lt;br/&gt;
Tomcat.exe seems to be OK even when I use the Power User account.&lt;br/&gt;
Environment variables are system-wide, there are no differences between&lt;br/&gt;
accounts&apos; PATH or CATALINA_HOME . There might be some registry subtlety - the&lt;br/&gt;
only difference I&apos;ve seen is that the Power User had no branch under&lt;br/&gt;
HKCU/Software for &quot;Apache Software Foundation&quot;. I had it manually added to the&lt;br/&gt;
Power User (complete content, with export from Admn and merge from PowerUser)&lt;br/&gt;
and still couldn&apos;t launch the Service Manager.&lt;br/&gt;
The installer is wrong, autostarting Service Manager for all the users. (there&lt;br/&gt;
are Users accounts that cannot control a service AFAIK). But this is another bug&lt;br/&gt;
and I will file it separately. Power Users are able to control the services.&lt;br/&gt;
I am using v5.5.4.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12408145" author="lucisandor@gmail.com" created="Thu, 27 Jan 2005 11:37:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Anyway... installation fails because a User cannot install a service.&lt;br/&gt;
Either close the bug and consider it a mistake of the user, or, better, file a&lt;br/&gt;
new bug for the installer: non-administrative users are not allowed to install&lt;br/&gt;
services and the installer should not let them believe they can do it. The&lt;br/&gt;
installer should check for administrative rights and act consequently.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12408146" author="mturk@apache.org" created="Sun, 17 Apr 2005 18:31:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You will need to start the tomcat5.exe with the proper service name&lt;br/&gt;
if they are different then &apos;Tomcat5&apos;.&lt;br/&gt;
If your service is named Tomcat5a then you can either rename the&lt;br/&gt;
tomcat5.exe to tomcat5a.exe or use &apos;tomcat5.exe //TS//Tomcat5a&apos;&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="12408147" author="ljh68@hotmail.com" created="Fri, 15 Jul 2005 04:20:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It used to work with my j2sdk 1.4.2. Now I have the same problem after I &lt;br/&gt;
upgraded to j2sdk 1.4.2_08 on my Windows XP professional. The following is the &lt;br/&gt;
output when running tomcat5.exe from a command window: &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;2005-07-14 12:00:00&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;349  prunsrv.c&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;error&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
The system cannot find the file specified.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;2005-07-14 12:00:00&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1037 prunsrv.c&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;error&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Load configuration failed&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12832586" author="mturk@apache.org" created="Thu, 11 Feb 2010 17:30:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We don&apos;t support Java 1.4&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    </comments>
