<item>
            <title>[DAEMON-13] [daemon] invalid execve() usage</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DAEMON-13</link>
                <project id="12310468" key="DAEMON">Commons Daemon</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As revealed by strace, jsvc tries to reexec itself without using full&lt;br/&gt;
path. This causes jsvc to be unusable.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;jsvc is installed under /usr/bin/jsvc and during starting jsvc&lt;br/&gt;
it is reexecuted as just jsvc and therefore not found if not&lt;br/&gt;
in the /usr/bin directory.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please see debian bug report for a strace&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://bugs.debian.org/cgi-bin/bugreport.cgi?bug=314937&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://bugs.debian.org/cgi-bin/bugreport.cgi?bug=314937&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Wolfgang&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Operating System: Linux&lt;br/&gt;
Platform: Other&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
        <key id="12342431">DAEMON-13</key>
            <summary>[daemon] invalid execve() usage</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=21133&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Bug</type>
                                            <priority id="2" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/priorities/critical.svg">Critical</priority>
                        <status id="6" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/statuses/closed.png" description="The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are not closed can be reopened.">Closed</status>
                    <statusCategory id="3" key="done" colorName="green"/>
