More complete patch.  Use this one instead.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12405145" author="william.barker@wilshire.com" created="Mon, 22 Sep 2003 04:21:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I missed a regression on the last patch (but, with the source files messed up, &lt;br/&gt;
they are hard to read &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12405146" author="remm@apache.org" created="Mon, 22 Sep 2003 15:21:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I am not affected by this bug, since the JDK 1.4 logger internationalizes the&lt;br/&gt;
log format (stupid morons), therefore it is not parsed, and it doesn&apos;t crash.&lt;br/&gt;
So sorry, there&apos;s no way I could have caught this regression. I&apos;ll try to&lt;br/&gt;
convince the JDK to use the default locale for future releases &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12405147" author="william.barker@wilshire.com" created="Thu, 25 Sep 2003 10:40:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Created an attachment (id=8347)&lt;br/&gt;
Restore previous copy-over behavior&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12405148" author="remm@apache.org" created="Sat, 27 Sep 2003 19:15:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I finally was able to reproduce it, by doing a System.out (trying to open the&lt;br/&gt;
