                                    <watches>0</watches>
                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12407200" author="mturk@apache.org" created="Wed, 11 Aug 2004 13:46:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for spotting that.&lt;br/&gt;
This is fixed in the CVS right now.&lt;br/&gt;
You may test the new binaries from&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://cvs.apache.org/viewcvs.cgi/jakarta-tomcat-connectors/procrun/bin/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://cvs.apache.org/viewcvs.cgi/jakarta-tomcat-connectors/procrun/bin/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, small tip.&lt;br/&gt;
Since you are already using environment vars, you may use:&lt;br/&gt;
set PR_DISPLAYNAME=E-NetAware Web Service&lt;br/&gt;
It is equivalent to:&lt;br/&gt;
--DisplayName &quot;E-NetAware Web Service&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Any option except service name can be used as environment variable&lt;br/&gt;
prefixed with &apos;PR_&apos;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    </comments>
