&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="12405955" author="remm@apache.org" created="Tue, 10 Feb 2004 22:28:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Tomcat will base its working path on catalina.home, and will work as expected.&lt;br/&gt;
I assume you want your own application to rely on the current path, which IMO is&lt;br/&gt;
very bad design. This is not a Tomcat issue anyway.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12405956" author="william.barker@wilshire.com" created="Wed, 11 Feb 2004 14:53:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed now in the CVS, and will appear in the next commons-daemon release.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12405957" author="sg_apache@pingbot.com" created="Sat, 6 Nov 2004 06:41:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I had the same problem and I have tried both the Beta 4.0.29 version of&lt;br/&gt;
tomcat5.exe and tomcat4w.exe and I tried the Alpha 5.5.4 version and the&lt;br/&gt;
WorkingPath option does not work for me.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here is the command that is installing the service:&lt;br/&gt;
set EXECUTABLE=%CATALINA_HOME%\bin\tomcat5.exe&lt;br/&gt;
set PR_DISPLAYNAME=Apache Tomcat&lt;br/&gt;
set PR_DESCRIPTION=Apache Tomcat Server - &lt;a href=&quot;http://jakarta.apache.org/tomcat&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://jakarta.apache.org/tomcat&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
set PR_INSTALL=%EXECUTABLE%&lt;br/&gt;
set PR_LOGPATH=%CATALINA_HOME%\logs&lt;br/&gt;
set PR_CLASSPATH=%CATALINA_HOME%\bin\bootstrap.jar&lt;br/&gt;
&quot;%EXECUTABLE%&quot; //IS//Tomcat5&lt;br/&gt;
--Jvm auto &lt;br/&gt;
--StartClass org.apache.catalina.startup.Bootstrap &lt;br/&gt;
--StopClass org.apache.catalina.startup.Bootstrap &lt;br/&gt;
--StartParams start &lt;br/&gt;
--StopParams stop &lt;br/&gt;
--WorkingPath &quot;C:/Tomcat&quot;&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="12405958" author="william.barker@wilshire.com" created="Sat, 6 Nov 2004 08:23:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The option is now called --StartPath&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
